import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['price'], bins=20, color='blue', alpha=0.7, label='Car Prices')
    plt.axvline(data['price'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['price'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Price')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of car prices?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.scatter(data['horsepower'], data['price'])
    plt.xlabel('Horsepower')
    plt.ylabel('Price')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between car price and horsepower?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['mileage'] = pd.to_numeric(data['mileage'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['mileage'])]
    
    plt.hist(data['mileage'], bins=20, color='blue', alpha=0.7, label='Car Mileage')
    plt.axvline(data['mileage'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['mileage'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Mileage')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of car mileage?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    body_style_counts = data['body_style'].value_counts()
    body_style_counts.plot(kind='bar', color=['blue', 'orange', 'green', 'red', 'purple'])
    plt.title('What is the distribution of car body styles?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Body Styles')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend(body_style_counts.index, title='Body Styles')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    scatter = ax.scatter(data['fuel_efficiency'], data['price'])
    ax.set_xlabel('Fuel Efficiency')
    ax.set_ylabel('Car Price')
    ax.set_title('What is the relationship between car price and fuel efficiency?')
    plt.legend(*scatter.legend_elements(), title='Cars')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
